31/05/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Two Bulgarian climbers died while climbing Mt Everest last week. A Russian expedition found the body of Hristo Hristov, 26, on 24 May. He perished shortly after reaching the summit without the use of oxygen. On Saturday (29 May), Brazilian climbers found the body of 43-year-old Mariana Maslarova. She was part of a Russian-Brazilian commercial expedition and had been unaccounted for since Tuesday. (AFP, Everestnews.com - 29/05/04)
